Operational reporting should answer a simple question: what needs action now?

Teams often produce reports that describe performance but do not guide next steps. Decision-oriented reporting highlights deviations, explains context, and points to ownership.

## What decision-ready reports include

- Current performance vs target
- Root-cause indicators
- Impact on service or delivery
- Recommended follow-up by owner

## Meeting-level impact

When reports are structured for action, review meetings spend less time on interpretation and more time on execution.
